  CCOOLLOORRSS

    If you want to be able to view your clock in color, include the following
    in the #ifdef COLOR section you read with xxrrddbb(1X11R5):

    *customization:                 -color

    This will cause oocclloocckk to pick up the colors in the app-defaults color
    customization file: //uussrr//lliibb//XX1111//aapppp--ddeeffaauullttss//CClloocckk--ccoolloorr. The default
    colors are as follows:

    Clock*Background: grey
    Clock*BorderColor: light blue
    Clock*hour: yellow
    Clock*jewel: yellow
    Clock*minute: yellow

